# STEP BY STEP WALLET GENERATION GUIDE OF OCTRA { CODESPACE }

---

## ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Install Bun

```bash 
curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash source ~/.bashrc bun --version
```
---

##ðŸ”¹ Step 2:Open terminal in gitpod and install Python
```bash
 sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv python3-dev -y
```
---
##ðŸ”¹ Step 3:Run these commands :
```
bash git clone https://github.com/octra-labs/octra_pre_client.git cd octra_pre_client python3 -m venv venv source venv/bin/activate # for windows use: venv\Scripts\activate pip install -r requirements.txt cp wallet.json.example wallet.json
```
---
##ðŸ”¹ Step 4:Open wallet.json
```
bash nano wallet.json
```
---
##ðŸ”¹ Step 5:Edit it (change placeholders to your wallet data):
```json
 { "priv": "private-key-here", "addr": "octxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx", "rpc": "https://octra.network" }
```
---
ðŸ”¹ Step 6:Run to open frontend UI to make transaction

```bash
 ./run.sh
```
